<otsl><loc_69><loc_42><loc_435><loc_171><ched>Governance Level<ched>SPECIAL HRMPSB (Teaching Position)<nl><fcel>Schools Division Office; and School<fcel>Chairperson: a. Assistant Schools Division Superintendent Members: b Chief of the Curriculum Implementation Division School Head where the vacancy exists d Administrative Officer V for the Administrative Services Section Administrative Officer IV (HRMO) f: Representative of accredited employee's union/ association belonging to the teaching group Secretariat: Selected personnel from HR/ Administrative Services Section as designated by the HRMPSB Chair<nl></otsl>
<text><loc_48><loc_184><loc_457><loc_201>33. A majority of the HRMPSB shall constitute a quorum; provided that the Chairperson is present.</text>
<unordered_list><list_item><loc_78><loc_205><loc_387><loc_215>During the comparative assessment; HRMPSB shall observe the following:</list_item>
<list_item><loc_91><loc_220><loc_369><loc_230>Convene the applicants in a group to witness the paper evaluation;</list_item>
<list_item><loc_74><loc_240><loc_458><loc_264>c Assess; deliberate, and rate the applicants' competencies on the Classroom Observable Strands /Indicators through the conduct of classroom observation following the rubrics and protocols provided in this Order;</list_item>
